This(command-line build) is just for debugging/testing.  It may not work 
properly.

sexycat is an even more trivial tool that writes the raw PCM sound to STDOUT.
Pipe it into aplay or artscat to hear it. (Format S16_LE, stereo, 44.1KHz)

sexyao is another test program that uses the libao library to output sound.
It has been confirmed to work on Linux, MacOS X, and Windows (using Cygwin).
